<subSubSection id="F896EDA8C97C6329FF07FF778B30FE8B" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B033BE23C97C6329FF07FF778B30FE8B" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="82F86231C97C6329FF07FF778B7EFF16" bold="true" box="[189,328,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is named after the renowned writer in Malayalam poetry, who stood with her strong words for mother Nature and conservation of natural resources, Padmasree Smt. Sugathakumari. She was at the forefront of environmental and feminist movements in 
<collectingRegion id="724870C1C97C6329FD41FF0F8970FEAE" box="[763,838,230,256]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Kerala</collectingRegion>
and played a prominent role in the save Silent Valley movement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F896EDA8C97C6329FF07FEC78BD7FE1B" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B033BE23C97C6329FF07FEC78BD7FE1B" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="82F86231C97C6329FF07FEC78BC4FEE6" bold="true" box="[189,498,302,328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—So far, the new species is collected only from the 
<typeStatus id="6F370081C97C6329FBEEFEC68EB2FEE7" box="[1108,1156,303,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">type</typeStatus>
locality of Mattumala, in Nelliyampathy hills of 
<collectingRegion id="724870C1C97C6329FE31FEBB8BE0FEC2" box="[395,470,338,364]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Kerala</collectingRegion>
at an elevation of 
<quantity id="777413C6C97C6329FD1EFEBB8908FEC3" box="[676,830,338,365]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="1100.0">1100–1200 m</quantity>
a.s.l. 
<taxonomicName id="778CC5A0C97C6329FC3AFEBA8E99FEC2" box="[896,1199,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Tripogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sugathakumariae">
<emphasis id="82F86231C97C6329FC3AFEBA8E99FEC2" box="[896,1199,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Tripogon sugathakumariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found growing in open montane grasslands along with 
<taxonomicName id="778CC5A0C97C6329FD99FE9E89A5FE3E" authority="Roemer &amp; Schultes" authorityName="Roemer &amp; Schultes" authorityYear="1817" box="[547,915,374,401]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Tripogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bromoides">
<emphasis id="82F86231C97C6329FD99FE9E8884FE3E" box="[547,690,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">T. bromoides</emphasis>
Roemer &amp; Schultes
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="778CC5A0C97C6329FC72FE9F8BEBFE1B" authority="(Linnaeus 1753: 745) De Candolle (1825: 352)" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityPageNumber="352" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="745" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Alysicarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bupleurifolius">
<emphasis id="82F86231C97C6329FC72FE9F8ED9FE3E" box="[968,1263,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Alysicarpus bupleurifolius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D41DC3D2C97C6329FB47FE9F8A85FE1B" author="Linnaeus, C." pageId="4" pageNumber="105" refId="ref2414" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species plantarum. Vol 2. Holmiae: Impensis Laurentii Salvii, London. 639 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus 1753: 745</bibRefCitation>
) De 
<bibRefCitation id="D41DC3D2C97C6329FF50FE738BEBFE1B" author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[234,477,410,437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" refId="ref2172" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1825) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, sive, Enumeratio contracta ordinum generum specierumque plantarum huc usque cognitarium, juxta methodi naturalis, normas digesta. Vol 2. Parisii: Sumptibus Sociorum Treuttel et Wu ¨ rtz. 644 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 286" type="book" year="1825">Candolle (1825: 352)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
